title: Geoffrey Keezer - Rhythm Changes Workout (Preview)
description: Available at https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - Next to the blues, Gershwin's "I Got Rhythm" is undoubtedly the most commonly played song form in jazz music. Designed for more advanced improvisers, this 2-part lesson explores creative ways to apply substitute chord changes over both the 'A' and 'B' sections, including Nat Cole's "Bop-Kick", George Coleman's "Lo-Joe", Sonny Stitt's "Eternal Triangle" and several wild and wooly hybrids, even an 'A' section that incorporates John Coltrane's "Countdown"! Great for any instrument. (Level: Advanced)
